01/12/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Romania has registered its highest trade deficit ever, the National Institute of Statistics reported on Wednesday (30 November). 
The deficit jumped to 1.4 billion euros in October, to reach 7.73 billion euros for the first ten months of the year.
In other news, the World Bank's board of directors has endorsed a $60m loan to implement the so-called Knowledge Economy project. 
It is aimed at increasing access to the Internet across Romania, especially computer and Internet access outside major cities. 
(Rompres - 01/12/05; AFX, AP - 30/11/05)
